BEIJING, Dec. 17 (Xinhua) -- Domestic adventure movie "Schemes in Antiques" on Thursday continued leading the Chinese mainland box office chart, data from the China Movie Data Information Network showed Friday. Adapted from a novel of the same name, the movie tells a story of a series of adventures of the main characters to find out the truth surrounding a Buddha head from the Tang Dynasty (618-907). It earned 9.2 million yuan (around 1.4 million U.S. dollars) on Thursday. Domestic comedy-suspense film "Be Somebody" ranked second on the box office chart, raking in 6.5 million yuan on Thursday. It was followed by romantic movie "Good Night Beijing," which pocketed about 2.1 million yuan. Enditem